news.title: Arvind Smartspaces' net profit dips 14.53% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Arvind Smartspaces' consolidated total income stood at Rs 55.22 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 22.90 per cent from Rs 44.93 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Puravankara's sales bookings up 20% to Rs 796 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Sales bookings stood at Rs 796 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal as against Rs 666 crore in the year-ago period. In terms of volumes, sales bookings rose 3 per cent to 1.02 million square feet from 0.99 million square feet.

news.title: Vishakapatnam: CBI books granite company in Rs 3 crore loan fraud case
news.para: A case was filed against Akshara Kartheka Granites and its managing director Kesani Yedukondulu and director Kesani Rajarajeswari following a complaint filed by Kota Kalyanai, general manager of Canara Bank, Circle Office, Vijayawada.

news.title: NGT imposes Rs 68-crore fine on 343 stone crushers in Haryana's Charkhi Dadri
news.para: The order came on a petition by local resident Vinod Kumar Jangra, who alleged that dust and dirt from the stone crushers were adversely affecting the environment and public health.

news.title: Defense minister, Madhya Pradesh CM distribute free land to 25,000 poor in Singrauli
news.para: The union defense minister further said that a very virtuous work has been done in Madhya Pradesh by allotting land free of cost to poor families for housing.

news.title: Ludhiana: LIT chairman demands one-time settlement of non-construction dues
news.para: The chairman had put up these demands in a recent meeting held with local bodies minister Dr Inderbir Singh Nijjar, where chairmen from other districts were also present.

news.title: E-payment for Cidco housing scheme till January 31
news.para: However, applicants are informed that there has been a slight change in the date of computerised draw, which will now be held on February 10 instead of February 8.

news.title: DMRC appointed consultant for Jaipur Metro extension
news.para: Earlier, when the 9.1-km stretch of Metro Line 1A was constructed between Mansarovar and Badi Chaupar, the state government had appointed DMRC as the consulting agency.

news.title: Maharashtra plans to convert plot marked for zoo to residential zone in Mumbai
news.para: BMC approved the change in December and its development plan (DP) department has invited suggestions and objections from the public for the proposed change, reports Chaitanya Marpakwar.

news.title: Meet to fix structural flaws at 15 highrises in Gurugram likely this week
news.para: The structural audit report, submitted by the four agencies to the district administration, revealed that the basements of most of the projects have seepage and flooding apart from issues like falling of concrete, corrosion of steel and others.

news.title: Amway Global's CEO sells flat in Gurugram for Rs 19 crore
news.para: According to market sources, the apartment is approximately 6,500 sq ft in size and was sold for about Rs 30,000 per sq ft in October last year.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP scraps OC of Sobha City for submitting fabricated documents
news.para: The urban planning department of the civic body in its order stated that Sobha Limited had obtained the OC for its Sobha City project by producing fabricated documents.

news.title: Maharashtra RERA eases lapsed project extension norm
news.para: A project is considered "lapsed" when the developer does not adhere to the timeline mentioned at the time of registration. Once a project is declared "lapsed", the developer concerned cannot advertise for it. The state has over 4,500 lapsed projects.

news.title: Haryana: RWAs ask for a rethink on order to keep gates open
news.para: This comes after the HSVP recently issued a notice to the sector RWAs, directing them to keep all the main colony gates open, especially during the daytime, and at least one gate open 24X7 with a guard on duty.

news.title: Centre likely to release Rs 566 crore for third metro line by March in Pune
news.para: The total cost of the Hinjewadi-Shivajinagar third Metro line project is Rs8,313 crore, including land acquisition and rehabilitation components.
